The #CrowdStrike Outage Cost Delta Air Lines an Estimated $500 Million

Delta Air Lines experienced a significant operational disruption due to a CrowdStrike-caused outage on July 19, 2024, resulting in approximately 7,000 flight cancellations over five days. 

The outage led to an estimated $500 million in damages, prompting Delta to pursue legal claims against CrowdStrike and Microsoft. 

The financial impact includes a $380 million loss in revenue for the September quarter, primarily due to refunds and customer compensation. Additionally, the incident incurred $170 million in non-fuel expenses related to customer reimbursements and crew costs, while fuel expenses were reduced by $50 million due to the flight cancellations.

üî∞ HOW TO CRACK ANY HASH ‚é† DETAILED DEHASHING GUIDE üî∞


This guide is super simple and doesn't require time wasting tools, such as Hashcat or any
other time consuming methods. With this method, we will be using hashes.com, a hash
cracking service which all you do is paste you list of hashes into a text box and wait for
your hashes to be checked against a huge list. The hashes.com website supports almost all
hashes (including ones with salt) and is perfect for anyone looking for a quick and easy
solution to hash cracking.

To get started, we first need a combo or list of hashes (make sure it is parsed already for
an easy time). Combos can be parsed in many ways, CSV being the most common. Some examples
of an already parsed combo is one having deliminator. Now, hashes.com offers two types of
cracking, either searching already cracked hashes (mass search & free search), or using the
escrow, which allows you to upload your list of hashes that you want cracked. But first, we
will start with the hash search.



1 - We need to extract the hashes from the combo. One editing tool I use is a tool called
EmEditor (https://www.emeditor.com/). EmEditor is really great for editing files/combos.

2 - Now that we have the combo open, there should be a "CSV/Sort option" on the toolbar of
EmEditor.

The deliminator in the combo I have chosen is a comma which should be "Comma Separated" in
the tool (don't worry if your deliminator is not there). To add a new deliminator, you just
need to right-click on the tool -> Customize CSV -> Add -> Deliminator, then pick your own
deliminator

3 - Now, time to extract the hashes from the combo. Simply click on your deliminator choice
in the "CSV/Sort", whether it be comma or your own custom one. In my case, it's just comma
separated. 

When we choose our sorting, each section will appear; we want our hashes. Simply click on top
of the column for hashes -> right-click -> copy columns.

4 - Once we have copied the columns, create a new document and paste the column we copied into
the new document and save.

5 (only applies to salt) - If your combo contains a salt, step back to step 4, Hold SHIFT,
click the top of both columns, then copy columns. When pasting into new file, click search ->
replace -> find your deliminator (if the delim is ":" don't change), put it in find, then in
replace, put in ":".

6 - Now that we have our hashes file, head over to hashes.com -> Decrypt hashes -> Mass Search.

7 - Now, choose our hashes file, hit submit, and wait as it's processed.

8 - Once it's processed, download founds and there are the cracked hashes :)
